    Why do snowboarders wear mittens?
    Many snowboarders wear mittens because they don't need the extra dexterity to hold poles and can benefit from the greater warmth that mittens provide. Many snowboards also wear gloves and it certainly makes taking off and putting on bindings at the start and end of each run easier.Oct 7, 2021
